{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Log entries with the same trace ID are grouped together regardless of which microservice emitted them.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The real failure boundary is the wiring between ingestion/parsing and correlation across heterogeneous service records. A unit test on grouping logic alone can miss field-mapping or normalization mismatches between modules.","test_description":"Run the ingest + normalize + correlate pipeline on a mixed dataset from multiple services where shared trace IDs appear in different service-specific records; assert each output trace group contains all expected entries across services with no cross-trace contamination.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The timeline view orders entries by timestamp, correctly handling clock skew of up to 500ms between services.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Correctness depends on timestamp parsing/normalization plus ordering logic together. A pure sort-function unit test could miss real skew-handling failures introduced at module boundaries (format/timezone/precision handling).","test_description":"Feed multi-service logs with controlled timestamp skew (including boundary cases near 500ms) through the timeline-building pipeline and verify final ordering matches expected causal order under the skew tolerance rule.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A latency spike (p99 above 3x the baseline) is detected and flagged in the anomaly report.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure risk is in the composed metrics path: baseline computation, percentile aggregation, threshold comparison, and report emission. Unit tests for each statistic can still miss end-to-end threshold/report wiring bugs.","test_description":"Execute metrics aggregation and anomaly-report generation on synthetic traffic with a known baseline and an injected high-latency tail that pushes p99 beyond 3x; assert the spike is flagged in the produced anomaly report with the correct metric context.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.4,"Integration":0.5,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Malformed JSON log entries are skipped without crashing the pipeline, and the count of skipped entries is reported.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failures are usually exception-propagation and accounting issues across parser + pipeline stages. Mocking or unit-testing parser behavior alone can hide crashes or miscounts in actual stage composition.","test_description":"Run the real ingestion pipeline over a batch containing valid and intentionally malformed JSON lines; assert process completion without crash, all valid entries still flow through, and skipped-entry count equals malformed-entry count.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The tool handles a burst of 10,000 log entries per second without dropping entries or falling behind.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This depends on real runtime behavior (I/O throughput, buffering, scheduling, backpressure, possible subprocess/runtime limits). In-process mocks can easily hide drops, queue saturation, or lag under load.","test_description":"Run the deployed executable/service under a real load generator that emits 10,000 structured log entries/sec for a sustained interval; measure ingest vs processed counts and processing lag over time, and fail if any drops occur or backlog grows beyond allowed bounds.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
